snippet: South Korean managers returned Monday to the Kaesong industrial complex in the latest sign of a thaw on the divided Korean Peninsula.
abstract: Hundreds of cars and trucks stream across the border to take South Korean managers and raw materials back to a jointly operated industrial park in Kaesong, North Korea, where factories resume production after a 166-day hiatus; it is the latest sign of thaw on the divided Korean Peninsula.
lead_paragraph: South Korean managers returned Monday to the Kaesong industrial complex in the latest sign of a thaw on the divided Korean Peninsula.

headline.main: Jointly Run Factory Park in North Korea Resumes Production
